description: Borrowed from Latin excribere; ex (“out, from”) + scribere (“to write”).

verbs.description: exscribe (third-person singular simple present exscribes, present participle exscribing, simple past and past participle exscribed)

examples: I that have been a lover, and could show it/ Though not in these, in rhymes not wholly dumb/ Since I exscribe your sonnets, am become/ A better lover, and much better poet.
